sequenceDiagram
    actor "Client Contact's Browser" as ClientContactsBrowser
    participant "Frontend SPA" as FrontendSPA
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL Database" as PostgreSQLDatabase

    activate FrontendSPA
    ClientContactsBrowser->>FrontendSPA: 1. 1. GET /approve-milestone/{token} User clicks the secure link in the email.
    FrontendSPA-->>ClientContactsBrowser: HTML/JS/CSS for the approval page.
    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 2. 2. GET /api/v1/milestone-approvals/{token} On page load (useEffect), validate token and fetch milestone details.
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK with MilestoneDetailsDTO or 4xx/5xx error.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 3. 2a. SELECT * FROM ActionTokens WHERE token_hash = HASH(token) AND expires_at > NOW() AND used_at IS NULL
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Token record or NULL.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 4. 2b. SELECT p.Name, m.Description FROM Milestones m JOIN Projects p ON m.ProjectId = p.Id WHERE m.Id = {milestoneId_from_token}
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Milestone details.
    FrontendSPA->>ClientContactsBrowser: 5. 3. Render Milestone Details & Action Buttons Displays project name, milestone description, and 'Approve'/'Reject' buttons.
    ClientContactsBrowser->>FrontendSPA: 6. 4. Click 'Approve' Button
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 7. 5. POST /api/v1/milestone-approvals/{token}/approve Submit the approval action.
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK or 4xx/5xx error.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 8. 5a. BEGIN TRANSACTION
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: OK
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 9. 5b. SELECT ... FOR UPDATE Re-validate token and milestone status with pessimistic lock.
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Locked token record.
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 10. 5c. UPDATE Milestones SET status = 'Approved' WHERE id = {milestoneId}
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: OK
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 11. 5d. UPDATE ActionTokens SET used_at = NOW() WHERE id = {tokenId}
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: OK
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 12. 5e. INSERT INTO AuditLogs (UserId, Action, ...) Log the approval event.
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: OK
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDatabase: 13. 5f. COMMIT TRANSACTION
    PostgreSQLDatabase-->>BackendAPI: OK
    FrontendSPA->>ClientContactsBrowser: 14. 6. Render Success Confirmation Displays a message like 'Thank you! The milestone has been approved.'

    note over BackendAPI: Token Security: The token is a short-lived JWT containing milestoneId, clientContactId, and an ex...
    note over BackendAPI: Idempotency & Race Conditions: The API must use a database transaction with SELECT ... FOR UPDATE...
    note over FrontendSPA: A separate flow for 'Reject' would be similar but would include a 'reason' in the POST body and u...

    deactivate BackendAPI
    deactivate FrontendSPA
